WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.360
In the Adding Co-Instructors and Teaching Assistants video, we saw how to add members

00:00:08.360 --> 00:00:12.680
to our workspace one by one, but what if we want to add a large number of individuals

00:00:12.680 --> 00:00:14.720
to our space at once?

00:00:14.720 --> 00:00:18.719
There are several ways to add multiple members to your workspace at once, and in this video

00:00:18.719 --> 00:00:21.520
we'll go through the sharing link option.

00:00:21.520 --> 00:00:25.360
Please check out the RS Cloud Package video if you're interested in learning how to

00:00:25.360 --> 00:00:29.780
add multiple members via the RStudio Cloud API.

00:00:29.780 --> 00:00:34.000
To add multiple individuals to our workspace, let's click on the Members button at the

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:39.060
top of our workspace, and then click on Options to open the Access menu.

00:00:39.060 --> 00:00:43.380
From here, let's invite multiple individuals using the sharing link.

00:00:43.380 --> 00:00:48.060
This method will give us a link that we can distribute via email or on a course webpage,

00:00:48.060 --> 00:00:53.139
allowing all of our learners to access the workspace on RStudio Cloud.

00:00:53.139 --> 00:00:57.259
For the initial role, we'll choose Contributor, and then take a look at the permissions at

00:00:57.259 --> 00:00:59.119
the bottom of the page.

00:00:59.119 --> 00:01:03.520
We can choose what contributors are allowed to do within the workspace by selecting or

00:01:03.520 --> 00:01:06.199
deselecting the options presented.

00:01:06.199 --> 00:01:10.919
Once we've made our selections, we can click on Copy Sharing Link and distribute it as

00:01:10.919 --> 00:01:13.199
needed.

00:01:13.199 --> 00:01:17.320
Once all of our learners have joined the shared workspace, we can disable the existing link

00:01:17.320 --> 00:01:22.519
by resetting the sharing link or by setting our workspace to Invitation Required, which

00:01:22.519 --> 00:01:27.360
will mean new learners to the workspace will have to be added via the Add Member button

00:01:27.360 --> 00:01:29.919
from within the Members section of our workspace.

